Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
timing_cppr_e...ransition_mode(25.10)    timing_cppr_e...ransition_mode(25.10)

Name
       timing_cppr_enable_mismatch_transition_mode

Syntax
       timing_cppr_enable_mismatch_transition_mode {true | false}

       Default: true

       Enables CPPR compatibility mode when transitions mismatch at the common
       pin.

       This global variable controls the CPPR adjustment calculations that are
       computed  at the common pin when transitions for the launch and capture
       paths mismatch at the common pin. The following case scenarios are pos-
       sible:

              * The launch and capture clocks at the common pin are  different
                but match the launch and capture clocks reaching the endpoint,
                or,  launch  and  capture clock at the common pin are same but
                different from the launch and capture clocks reaching the  end
                point.

              * The  launch  and capture clocks at the common pin are same and
                match the launch and capture clocks reaching the endpoint.

       The following examples show the behavior  for  CPPR  computations  when
       this global variable is set to true:

              * Consider  a  launch  path with clock CK1, late rise transition
                and a capture path with clock GCK1  (related  to  CK1),  early
                fall  transition. The CPPR adjustment is computed by consider-
                ing the late fall from clock CK1 and  early  rise  from  clock
                GCK1.

                When  set to false (default), the software considers late fall
                from clock GCK1 and early rise from clock CK1.

              * Consider a launch path with clock CK1,  late  rise  transition
                and  a capture path with clock CK1, early fall transition. The
                CPPR adjustment is computed by considering the late fall  from
                the  launch phase of CK1 and early rise from the capture phase
                of CK1.

                When set to false, the software considers the late  fall  from
                capture phase of CK1 and early rise from launch phase of CK1.

       The CPPR adjustment is the minimum of the two CPPR adjustments computed
       for the rise and fall transitions.

       All the other combinations of the launch and capture transitions at the
       common  pin  for  late and early paths will show similar changes to the
       CPPR adjustment computation - when set to true.

       To set this global variable, use the set command.

